' A SUCCESS_ON/RESULT expression ranges over the function's ABI slot names and
' its ABI return name. An identifier naming neither is rejected (plan-50-I).
'
' Before plan-50-I this compiled clean: lowering mapped EVERY identifier onto one
' nameless "the native return" variable, so `SUCCESS_ON typo = 0` silently meant
' `SUCCESS_ON status = 0` — a gate that reads nothing like what it says.
LINK "demo" AS demoLink
  FUNC probe(n AS Integer) AS Boolean
    SYMBOL "demo_probe"
    ABI (n CInt32) AS status CInt32
    SUCCESS_ON typo = 0
    RESULT status = 1
  END FUNC
END LINK
